__NAME__ purpose
control access to SOAP features
__END__

__NAME__ synopsis
<arg choice='plain'><replaceable>subject</replaceable></arg>
<arg choice='plain'><replaceable>permission</replaceable></arg>
__END__

__NAME__ description
Defines which SOAP features are allowed.
__END__

__NAME__ notes
The global settings take precedence. For example, allowing actions in the
catalog configuration with <code>SOAP_Control Action always</code> only
works when the global configuration permit this feature as well.
__END__

__NAME__ see also
SOAP, SOAP_Action
__END__

__NAME__ example: Allow actions only
<programlisting>
SOAP_Control Action always
SOAP_Control Tag never
SOAP_Control Values never
SOAP_Control Database never
SOAP_Control Scratch never
</programlisting>
__END__
